I’m so excited to share a try on haul of Disco Daisies and answer some of your question below! 🪩🌼

Q: Why is the collection only available for 3 days or until sold out?
A: According to a 2020 Forbes article, around 30 - 40% of every apparel product made will remain unsold and ultimately end up in a landfill or be destroyed. My collection has no inventory, and every product will be made to order.

Q: How long will the products take to make?
A: Expect delivery in around 21 days

Q: Where can I buy it?
A: Online and a link will be posted here tomorrow!

Q: Will there be any special promotions?
A: YES, if you buy 2, you get 1 free! The discount code will be posted tomorrow. There will also be free shipping on orders over $100. 

Q; What happens if I order the wrong size?
A: There is a comprehensive size chart, and all products are made with stretch. A full refund is available within 14 days of delivery.

Q: Will you ship worldwide?
A: Yes, we ship to most countries.

Feel free to DM any other questions, and I will answer them for you!
#discodaisies #tryonhaul #haul

Hi! Story time below - I have had so much fun this past few weeks (6 months really) working on Disco Daisies and sharing it with you. Totally honest, my career has been rocky and before I started sharing dance videos and growing an audience, I didn’t have much success or virtue to my name. Having my own collection is something I never thought I’d be able to do. It’s a dream come true. 

Thank you so much for giving me the space to make opportunities like this happen for myself. If you’re a dancer or an artist I hope you’re inspired by my story and continue to chase your dreams… thank you thank you thank you for watching my videos and supporting my work!!! … love you all!

We just finished our 9 week program at @54d.nyc … How special it was, I can’t really explain to you. Luis and I have never done something like this together… I’m proud of myself but I’m more proud of him. He didn’t think he could find the motivation to do it, but he did. (Also his results are insannnnneeeeeeeee)

I’m starting a new chapter in my life that has a lot of uncertainty, and it was so nice to have something to be certain of everyday. Certain I was going to work hard, certain I was taking care of myself, certain I was going to see my amazing coaches and teammates.

Coaches @kevinpiedrahita91 and Luis… I so looked forward to seeing you every day. I had the most much fun and worked so hard. I can honestly say I’m in the best shape of my life. I will always think of you when I’m ready to give up, then I won’t. 

@jenmarienutrition ! I ate more healthy and beautiful foods the past 9 weeks than I ever have. Thank you for giving me a new perspective on taking care of myself as an athlete.

Hi friends! Here’s some things you might not know about me if you’re new to following my page 🤍🫶🏻 (📸 by @jontaylorphoto) 
- I’m from Greenville, SC but moved to NYC to dance 10 years ago!
- I struggled for many years to find steady work as a dancer and worked as a fitness instructor and personal trainer to support myself while auditioning
- I danced for the NBA Brooklyn Nets for 6 seasons and was captain for 4 seasons. Funnest job ever!
- I started making dance content in 2020 when I was unemployed. I gained 950k followers in under a year from sharing my passion and creativity! 
- Dancing and making content is full time work for me now. I see it as such a gift and I’m so thankful.
- I’m married and have 2 cats! You’ve probably seen them on my stories 😊 (Luis 👨🏻🇧🇷, Riddle 🐈‍⬛, and Wither 🐈)
- I’m so happy you’re here!
